{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Ey3AzJopE6sAgjVKjdUMaX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The dashboard is running with `--host=127.0.0.1 --port=8265` — it's bound to loopback only! This means it only accepts connections from within the pod itself, not from the Service. This is why the Service patch didn't fix it.\n\nThe ray start command also has `--include-dashboard=false`, but there's still a dashboard.py process running (weird). Let me re-read the command:\n\n```\nsh -c ray start --head --node-ip-address=\"${MY_POD_IP}\" --port=6379 --include-dashboard=false --num-cpus=0 --block\n```\n\nYet the dashboard is still listening on `127.0.0.1:8265` — it must be started separately by the entrypoint or ray launches it regardless of that flag. The real issue is that it's bound to loopback, so the Service can't reach it. I need to modify the Deployment to start the dashboard with `--host=0.0.0.0` instead. Let me check the Deployment configuration to see how ray is being invoked.\n```","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4431,"cache_read_input_tokens":30086,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4431},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e0bfc91b-9c35-4869-b4e0-d60264b32cc2","uuid":"6afaa815-ac97-4900-a53a-99851563b88e","request_id":"req_011CcQ4FQTgLD6Bh4QycyMQ1"}
